The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Archives
 The City Diary

																																																		Mandeep Kumar, 28, a resident of Punjab, was arrested at Calcutta airport on Sunday on his arrival from Bangkok. His wife had lodged a complaint of torture against him. He arrived in Calcutta on an Air India Express flight. Immigration officials said there was a look-out circular against him following the complaint lodged in September. Kumar said he had been to Bangkok to look for a job.
																																																		A vagrant entered the airports restricted area through a broken boundary wall on Sunday morning but was intercepted by CISF jawans while walking towards the runway. Police detained him for four hours.
																																																		A youth died and another was injured in two mishaps at Barrackpore and Rajarhat on Sunday. Uday Mondal, 25, was hit by a bus on route 211on Rajarhat Road. He was taken to RG Kar Hospital and the bus was impounded. In Barrackpore, 25-year-old Sujit Podder was killed after a truck hit him on the Kalyani-Barrackpore Expressway. 
																																																		Sandhya Das and Monda Mondal from Birati were arrested for allegedly selling several girls to Mumbai brothels. 

